%% xstream streaming - Scenario 3: Seek
%% User drags the seek slider. If the target time is already buffered, play resumes.
%% Otherwise the controller snaps to the 5-minute chunk boundary and restarts streaming.
sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant U as User
    participant VP as VideoPlayer
    participant PC as PlaybackController
    participant SS as StreamingService
    participant BM as BufferManager
    participant V as video element
    participant GQL as GraphQL

    U->>VP: drag seek slider to t
    VP->>PC: seekTo(t)
    PC->>V: video.currentTime = t
    V-->>PC: seeking DOM event
    PC->>PC: handleSeeking

    alt target already buffered
        PC-->>V: resume naturally (no reload)
    else needs new chunk
        Note right of PC: snapTime = floor(t div 300) times 300
        PC->>SS: cancel
        PC->>BM: seek(snapTime)
        Note right of BM: SourceBuffer.remove all, set timestampOffset, set currentTime
        PC->>GQL: startTranscode(videoId, res, snapTime, snapTime+300)
        Note right of PC: re-enters Scenario 1 flow from here
    end
